WEBVTT

00:11.601 --> 00:12.566
Ross.

00:12.600 --> 00:13.768
Triple double,

00:13.803 --> 00:15.100
courtesy of
America's favorite burger chain.

00:15.134 --> 00:17.134
Louis won
the class-action suit?

00:17.169 --> 00:22.102
♪ 10,000 men of Harvard
want victory today ♪

00:22.137 --> 00:24.669
All: ♪ for they know that
o'er old Eli ♪

00:24.703 --> 00:27.237
♪ fair Harvard holds sway ♪

00:27.271 --> 00:31.572
♪ so we'll conquer
all old Eli's men ♪

00:31.607 --> 00:34.179
My favorite part.

00:34.214 --> 00:35.981
You don't know the lyrics,
do you?

00:37.216 --> 00:39.486
I don't even know the lyrics,
Louis.

00:39.520 --> 00:41.523
Now are we practicing law
down here,

00:41.558 --> 00:43.326
or auditioning
a chorus line?

00:43.361 --> 00:45.198
It's called
<i>esprit de corps.</i>

00:45.233 --> 00:47.903
And I just got a $100 million
jury award overturned.

00:47.937 --> 00:49.405
I don't have to overturn
awards like that

00:49.439 --> 00:51.408
because I've never lost one
in the first place.

00:53.679 --> 00:55.147
So what is this,
a new cologne

00:55.181 --> 00:56.783
or just a hint of jealousy?

00:56.817 --> 00:57.920
I'm surprised you, uh,

00:57.954 --> 00:59.656
don't recognize
your wife's perfume.

00:59.690 --> 01:02.025
I know,
you're not married.

01:02.059 --> 01:04.962
It's still funny.

01:04.997 --> 01:06.330
You do realize
we're celebrating

01:06.365 --> 01:08.098
making fat people
even fatter, right?

01:08.133 --> 01:09.199
If you wanted
to do good,

01:09.234 --> 01:10.768
you should've been
a fake doctor.

01:12.405 --> 01:14.840
Business cards.

01:14.874 --> 01:16.508
Yup.

01:16.543 --> 01:18.812
My mistake is now official.
Come with me.

01:20.449 --> 01:23.719
And learn the goddamn lyrics
to the Harvard song, will ya?

01:23.753 --> 01:27.991
Oakhurst Capital has agreed to
a $200 million licensing deal.

01:28.025 --> 01:29.592
We are at the goal line.

01:29.627 --> 01:31.162
How are we
on brand protection?

01:31.196 --> 01:32.430
The contract is airtight.

01:32.464 --> 01:33.664
The only issue here

01:33.699 --> 01:36.102
is to get the Joyful Toy Company
to close.

01:36.136 --> 01:38.071
I'll go over it with Joy
one-on-one.

01:46.250 --> 01:48.051
- Uh...
- And if it does ring,

01:48.086 --> 01:49.152
you answer it.

01:49.186 --> 01:50.920
Oh. Yeah.

01:50.955 --> 01:52.422
Not in here.

01:52.456 --> 01:54.390
I--okay.

01:54.425 --> 01:56.492
Don't feel the need
to rush back when you're done.

01:56.527 --> 01:58.161
Who is this?

01:58.195 --> 01:59.562
Dude, it's Trevor.
Don't hang up.

01:59.596 --> 02:01.030
I only get one call.

02:01.064 --> 02:03.032
I'm in jail.

02:03.066 --> 02:04.500
I--I tried to hop this bus
at Port Authority.

02:04.534 --> 02:07.002
I was drunk.
It's all messed up.

02:07.037 --> 02:09.237
Look, I know we haven't talked
since we fought,

02:09.271 --> 02:12.641
but I didn't know
who else to call.

02:16.646 --> 02:18.747
Hey.

02:20.917 --> 02:24.387
I'm sorry, man.
I'm sorry.

02:24.422 --> 02:27.824
Okay.

02:27.859 --> 02:30.961
- I'm gonna pay you back.
- Yeah, you better.

02:30.996 --> 02:33.664
Your bail cost me
everything I have in the bank.

02:33.699 --> 02:34.732
The thing is,

02:34.767 --> 02:36.934
I don't have the money.

02:36.969 --> 02:38.336
What are you
talking about?

02:38.370 --> 02:40.538
You're clearing
$10,000 a month selling weed.

02:40.573 --> 02:42.040
It went out
as fast as it came in.

02:42.074 --> 02:43.909
Came in?

02:43.943 --> 02:46.144
I quit.
I'm not dealing anymore.

02:46.179 --> 02:49.014
- Bullshit.
- I'm serious.

02:49.048 --> 02:52.184
After we fought,
I don't know.

02:52.218 --> 02:54.420
Things just
started to fall apart.

02:54.454 --> 02:55.654
Jenny broke up with me.

02:59.025 --> 03:00.225
I didn't know.

03:00.259 --> 03:03.128
Well, I just realized
I needed to make a change.

03:03.162 --> 03:06.498
Even sold my bong.

03:06.532 --> 03:08.333
What have you done
with my friend?

03:08.367 --> 03:09.834
Yeah.
You should talk.

03:09.869 --> 03:11.769
Look at you. You look like
Gordon Gekko's little brother.

03:12.939 --> 03:14.506
What, are you
working on Wall Street, man?

03:14.540 --> 03:18.410
Why'd you call me,
Trevor?

03:18.445 --> 03:21.982
You're the one person
I knew would show up.

03:23.784 --> 03:27.288
You want to ask me
for anything...else?

03:27.322 --> 03:29.523
Look, all I care about
right now

03:29.558 --> 03:31.025
is keeping my record clean.

03:33.228 --> 03:35.063
You don't happen to know
any good lawyers, do ya?

03:38.234 --> 03:40.563
No. I don't.

